  <statement>
      
      
      
      
      
      <p>
          For each of the following, classify the type of variable described as <em>Numerical</em> or <em>Categorical</em>, as well as the subcategory <em>Continuous</em>, <em>Discrete</em>, <em>Nominal</em> or <em>Ordinal</em>.  Be sure to justify your choices.
          <ol>
              <li>The number of homicides in a city over a year.</li>
              <li>The average speed of drivers in a town between the hours of 8:00 am and 9:00 am.</li>
              <li>The amount of UV radiation a person is exposed to over a day.</li>
              <li>The number of freshman who smoke at a university.</li>
              <li>How many traffic accidents a city has over the next year.</li>
              <li>A job reference's rating of a candidate's punctuality from 1-5.</li>
          </ol>
          
      </p>
      
      
     
      
          
          
          
          
      
  </statement>
  <answer>
      <title>Partial Solution:</title>
      
      
      
      
     <p>
          <ol>
              <li>Numerical, Discrete</li>
              <li>Numerical, Continuous</li>
              <li>Numerical, Continuous</li>
              <li>Numerical, Discrete</li>
              <li>Numerical, Discrete</li>
              <li>Categorical, Ordinal</li>
          </ol>
          
      </p>
          
      
  </answer>
</exercise>
